text:
Video of the 31 Patriot Front members being taken out of the U-Haul and arrested for Criminal Conspiracy.
The U-Haul was stopped one block from the Pride in the Park event in Downtown Coeur d'Alene.

#update
From the interview with CDA Police Chief Lee White:
Over 30 people were arrested that are apart of Patriot Front. They had Patriot Front arm patches and hats. The group had riot gear including spears, shields, smoke grenades, and protective gear. They did not have any firearms that we are aware of at this point. There was one person from Idaho and the others from around the country.

The group loaded up in the Uhaul at a local Hotel and a concerned citizen called 911 to report what they saw. "It looked like a little army" the caller stated.

Two additional arrests occured from two people from Oregon in the City Park.
===

Prior post:
Large police presence on Northwest Boulevard in the area of Paul Bunyan.
Law enforcement has a U-Haul stopped and multiple people detained. Officers are searching the rear of the U-Haul wearing protective gear.

The road is partially closed.

We have asked Coeur d'Alene police for a statement on what is occurring.

#NorthIdahoNews

Just in case you don't know what makes this valley famous--or is it infamous? We are unique in all the world. A bit of Idocracy and LUDS Disease, but still unique.

Just another reason the Pocatello/Chubbuck School Board of Not- trusted Trustees think they can contaminate your children.

"Q: Are board members protected from civil suits? Are they above the law?

A: Generally a district carries insurance which entitles
a board member to be indemnified against the cost
of defending any civil or criminal action arising
out of the performance of his or her duties. Such
protection extends to criminal actions only if the
final disposition favors the member."

Source: Idaho "SchoolBoardCandidateInfo.pdf"

They need to be arrested, charged, and prosecuted as in criminal and civil lawsuits.

WOMEN'S LEAGUE OF VOTERS, DEMOCRATIC NATIONAL COMMITTEE (DNC), and the DEMOCRATIC CAUCUS HAVE IN COMMON? [Answer: Old Guard Suppression]

AVOIDANCE????? It is difficult for the People to have a voice, when the voices are suppressed. And I am not just referring to Jill Stein, or other Non-Blues and Reds. And I know first hand what control by suppression of the facts and truth is like. In fact, people simply break the laws to suppress the truth and facts in the Pocatello Valley and many others places, i.e. Arizona, Idaho, and now the DNC and NY.

And in this light we surely hope the the Pocatello League of Women Voters will not be suppressing the voice of the people and their right to run for office. Just because the Idaho Elections Office doesn't print a candidate on the ballot DOES NOT mean they are not already a declared candidate. The League of Women Voters can not decide who is worthy of representing the people of the Pocatello Valley and Bannock County.

With all the people running for office in the Pocatello Valley and Bannock County new venues will have to be sought if fairness is to be achieved in the election process. Government bodies and institutions that obstruct the election process are out-right breaking the law. And to name a few: ISU, City Of Pocatello (mayor and council), as well as School District #25 Pocatello Board of Trusties.

Things have to change and eliminating corruption is the main issue.

PS: How come it took almost 5 months to obtain a copy of the Pocatello League of Women's Voters' Pocatello City Council Debate, and in was the ONLY candidate forum open to everybody? Interesting, aeh!

PSS: How many people voted for Idaho Lorax to be a Democratic Socialist Delegate to the Idaho Conference standing for Bernie Sanders? A Lot! Anybody got the numbers? Is Idaho blocked from going by the Status Quo? Go ahead ask around.

text:
Will work for free

The beaver, in certain places, is better than a bulldozer, and far less expensive. "It's about $10,000 a hectare to replace wetlands, and you've got something to do it for free," Dr. Hood says. "The problem is that you also have something you can't control as easily as a backhoe." But this hasn't stopped several countries from trying to bring back the beaver. In Denmark, the European beaver was introduced in an area of planted pine forest where they got busy building dams and restoring the streams and rivers. (And making "beaver land" a popular tourist attraction.) In Scotland, the return of the beavers after 400 years has been more controversial, with salmon anglers, who fret over their stocks, pitted against conservationists, who believe in the rodents' environmental benefits. (In August, the first baby beavers were born.) In the United States, Wyoming offered beavers to landowners as a restoration strategy, and a similar plan is in the works in Oregon. "We humans like to engineer solutions to our environmental problems," says Steve Zack, a biologist with Wildlife Conservation Society in Oregon. "But meanwhile we have these beavers who do a spectacular job."

BREAKING NEWS: MONSANTO STRIKES AGAIN. This time in Idaho. Monsanto has agreed to pay $600,000 in fines for not reporting hundreds of uncontrolled releases of toxic chemicals, including hydrogen cyanide, sulfur dioxide, nitrogen oxides and mercury, at its Soda Springs, Idaho plant. "Each of these chemicals are hazardous and can pose serious health risks to workers and the community if mishandled or released in an uncontrolled manner," federal officials said in a statement.

Monsanto is just doing what they do so well: Contaminating and polluting. What’s new?

“As it says in the Bible, let the work I've done speak for me. Well, YOU (Judge Ketanji Brown Jackson) have spoken." -Senator Cory Booker

It moves me to tears to watch this amazing Black Man, Senator Booker, defend, advocate, & speak LIFE into the first Black Woman IN AMERICAN HISTORY be nominated for a seat on the Supreme Court.

Watch as he breaths life back into her battered soul from the absurd & vicious attacks from Racists senators taring at her credibility & her confidence.

Watch the whole video. It will show you the power of a Black Man covering, protecting, providing for a Black Women when she needs it the most.

This is what Healed Black Love looks like.

Please share in support of Judge Brown Jackson.

She needs us... right now.

Via PBS News Hour

Correction: some judges have integrity. Shall we name them?

Mike Saville for Idaho
March 24 at 7:45 PM ·

“H 782 Passed Idaho Senate 26 - 7.
POLITICIZING IDAHO COURTS

THIS IS THE MOST DANGEROUS BILL OF THE 2022 SESSION - or perhaps ANY session of the Idaho Legislature.

This bill (H782) will enable the governor to PACK THE COURTS with cronies, sycophants, and like-minded extremists. It politicizes the courts by putting political allies - by appointment - on the council that manages the process for appointing judges.

Call Governor Little and ask to Veto H 783
208-334-2100
